  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "dual_entrypoint_failure_contract_drift",
      "summary": "Context-aware and legacy entrypoints expose different failure behavior for the same background workflows.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/rectify/rectify.go",
        "goseg/routines/version.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/subsystem/subsystem_events.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`RectifyUrbit` logs `runTransitionEventLoopWithoutContext` failure and returns, while `RectifyUrbitWithContext` returns the error to callers.",
        "`StartVersionSubsystem` and `CheckVersionLoop` drop returned errors (`_ = ...WithContext(...)`), but their context variants propagate failures.",
        "`StartDockerSubsystemWithContext` returns listener/subscription errors, while `StartDockerHealthLoopsWithContext` starts background work with no error path to callers."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define one explicit contract for long-running services (either return errors or intentionally report through a shared health/error channel) and make non-context wrappers delegate without discarding failures. If suppression is intentional, centralize it in one top-level boundary and document it.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "background_loop_error_contracts"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "boundary_context_loss_after_logging",
      "summary": "Several boundaries log errors but return raw upstream errors, producing inconsistent diagnosability.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/state.go",
        "goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go",
        "goseg/leak/broadcast.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`GetStateJson` logs marshal failure and returns `err` directly (`return nil, err`) without operation context.",
        "`constructPierInfo` and `GetStartramServices` log failures and return raw errors (`return nil, err` / `return err`) instead of wrapping with boundary-specific context.",
        "`sendBroadcast` logs write failures and returns raw `err`, while neighboring code in the same subsystem often wraps errors with `%w` and explicit operation labels."
      ],
      "suggestion": "At package boundaries, either wrap with `%w` and operation context or return typed errors, but use one rule consistently. Remove duplicate log-and-return patterns by logging once at the top handling boundary and preserving wrapped chains for downstream inspection.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "error_context_propagation"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "wifi_not_found_error_typing_inconsistent",
      "summary": "Wi-Fi device-not-found failures mix sentinel and plain-string errors, making handling behavior path-dependent.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/system/wifi.go",
        "goseg/system/wifi_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`errWifiInterfaceNotFound` is defined and wrapped in `getConnectedSSIDWithRuntime`, enabling `errors.Is` checks.",
        "Other Wi-Fi discovery paths return ad-hoc strings for the same condition (`fmt.Errorf(\"no WiFi device found\")` and `fmt.Errorf(\"no WiFi device found: %w\", err)`), which are not normalized to the sentinel.",
        "Tests assert sentinel matching for one path (`errors.Is(err, errWifiInterfaceNotFound)`), but parallel paths do not guarantee that contract."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Normalize all no-device outcomes to a single exported sentinel/type (wrapped with `%w`), and update callers/tests to depend on `errors.Is`/`errors.As` rather than message text.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "error_typing_drift"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Parallel legacy/non-context APIs evolved without a single enforced failure contract.",
      "Error logging and error propagation responsibilities are split inconsistently across layers.",
      "Sentinel/typed error conventions are not uniformly applied within subsystems."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
